sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>(Browser)
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook<br/>Controller
    participant Kubelet as OpenShift Kubelet
    participant Quay as quay.io/modh<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>(Sidecar)
    participant Workbench as Workbench Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 1: Workbench Image Selection and Launch

    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench type<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth2/OIDC
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStreams<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Available images & annotations<br/>(opendatahub.io/notebook-image-*)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Notebook CR event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>+ HTTPRoute/Route<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Kubelet: Schedule pod
    Kubelet->>Quay: Pull image<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
    Quay-->>Kubelet: Container image (SHA256 digest)
    Note over Kubelet,Workbench: Pod starts with workbench container<br/>+ kube-rbac-proxy sidecar (RHOAI 3.x)<br/>or oauth-proxy sidecar (RHOAI 2.x)

    User->>Proxy: Access workbench<br/>HTTPS/443 via HTTPRoute/Route<br/>TLS terminated at ingress
    Proxy->>Proxy: Authenticate user<br/>(kube-rbac-proxy / oauth-proxy)
    Proxy->>Workbench: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888 (no auth, internal)
    Workbench-->>Proxy: JupyterLab / RStudio / code-server UI
    Proxy-->>User: Authenticated response

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 2: Konflux Image Build (PR)

    participant Dev as Developer
    participant GitHub as GitHub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PaC as Pipelines-as-Code
    participant Tekton as Tekton PipelineRun
    participant Registry as quay.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Dev->>GitHub: Open Pull Request<br/>HTTPS/443, GitHub Token
    GitHub-->>PaC: Webhook event
    PaC->>Tekton: Trigger PipelineRun<br/>(SA Token)
    Note over Tekton: git-clone -> buildah build<br/>-> SBOM generation<br/>-> image-index creation
    Tekton->>Registry: Push multi-arch image<br/>HTTPS/443, Push Secret
    Tekton->>GitHub: Report status<br/>HTTPS/443
